  "title": "M & E Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>1. Minimum Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical or its equivalent.</p><p>2. Min 6 to 10 years of Experience in Civil construction projects.</p><p>3. Carry out project planning, design, material requisition, cost control, project supervision and documentation.</p><p>4. Supervise the M & E works and coordinate with client’s representatives, consultants and sub-contractors to resolve any technical matters or site issues.</p><p>5. Attend site meetings with consultants.</p><p>6. Inform Project Director / Project Manager on any technical / site problems pertaining to M&E works.</p><p>7. Responsible for site supervision and coordination of M&E works with other trades such of civil, structural or architectural.</p><p>8. Prepare and arrange M&E installation in accordance with approved drawings and materials.</p><p>9. Coordinate & supervise M&E works carried out by sub-contractors that's in accordance to specifications, shop drawings, method statements and local codes & regulations.</p><p>10. Ensure site safety in accordance with safe work procedure.</p><p>12. Submission of M&E shop and coordinated drawings.</p><p>13. Coordination of sub-contractor's M&E work and ensuring the work is on schedule.</p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
